    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The current military posture and activity patterns suggest a focus on training, exercises, and strategic airlift operations. The Liaoning Carrier Strike Group is in the Western Pacific, while the JS Kaga is preparing for F-35B training with U.S. Marines. The USCGC Resolute is currently in port, with no reported deployments or exercises. Notable aircraft include the P-8 Poseidon, C-17 Globemaster III, and IL96, which are conducting maritime patrol, strategic airlift, and long-range transport missions. The overall assessment is that military activity is moderate, with a focus on readiness and preparedness. The introduction of the MQ-25A Stingray unmanned tanker and the development of the world&#39;s largest battleship are significant technological advancements. The data suggests a continued focus on regional security and cooperation, with an emphasis on maintaining readiness through exercises and technological advancements rather than large-scale force projection.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
